20/01/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- The US Embassy in Tirana and the US Justice Department are assisting the Albanian police by providing training on how to deal with forged documents, local media reported on Wednesday (January 19th). About 60 officers of the police's Border and Migration department have completed a training session in Durres that was led by representatives of the US Immigration and Customs Enforcement agency. The initiative will help Albania strengthen its border safety. (Lajmifundit, Klan, Telegrafi - 19/01/11) 
